Sentencas: A simple and cost-effective slip casting technique was successfully developed to fabricate NiO-YSZ anode substrates for tubular anode-supported single SOFCs.
Titulo: Slip casting combined with colloidal spray coating in fabrication of tubular anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An YSZ electrolyte film was coated on the anode substrates by colloidal spray coating technique.
Titulo: Slip casting combined with colloidal spray coating in fabrication of tubular anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A single cell, NiO-YSZ/YSZ (20 mu m)/LSM-YSZ, using the tubular anode supports with YSZ coating, was assembled and tested to demonstrate the feasibility of the techniques applied.
Titulo: Slip casting combined with colloidal spray coating in fabrication of tubular anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Using humidified hydrogen (75 ml/min) as fuel and ambient air as oxidant, the maximum power densities of the cell were 760 mW/cm(2) and 907 mW/cm(2) at 800 degrees C and 850 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Slip casting combined with colloidal spray coating in fabrication of tubular anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The observed OCV was closed to the theoretical value and the SEM results revealed that the microstructure of the anode fabricated by slip casting is porous while the electrolyte film coated by colloidal spray coating is dense.
Titulo: Slip casting combined with colloidal spray coating in fabrication of tubular anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells
